Brief acid hydrolysis (1 M acetic acid/15min/110 ◦ C) produced 4 distinct components (A, B, C and D), when examined by paper electrophoresis at pH 1.7 (
). Component A ( RmOG 0.57) had the same relative mobility and biological activity as agrocinopine D and also no longer reacted positively to the ketose sugar reagent of urea/phosphoric acid (
). The remaining components, B, C, D, were not formally identified.

